Package polyglot.ast

Class JLDel_c

java.lang.Object
polyglot.ast.JLDel_c
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, JLDel, NodeOps, Copy<JLDel>
@Deprecated
public class JLDel_c
extends java.lang.Object
implements JLDel, java.io.Serializable
Deprecated.
JL_c is the super class of JL node delegate objects. It defines default implementations of the methods which implement compiler passes, dispatching to the node to perform the actual work of the pass. Language extensions may subclass JL_c for individual node classes or may reimplement all compiler passes in a new class implementing the JL interface.

    • overrideContextVisit

      public Node overrideContextVisit​(Node parent, ContextVisitor visitor) throws SemanticException
      Deprecated.
      Description copied from interface: NodeOps
      Visit the context.

      This method is called by the override() method of the visitor. If this method returns non-null, the node's children will not be visited automatically. Thus, the method should check both the node this and it's children, usually by invoking visitChildren with tc or with another visitor, returning a non-null node. OR, the method should do nothing and simply return null to allow enter, visitChildren, and leave to be invoked on the node.

      The default implementation returns null. Overriding of this method is discouraged, but sometimes necessary.

      Specified by:
      overrideContextVisit in interface NodeOps
      visitor - context visitor
      Throws:
      SemanticException

      Remove any remaining ambiguities from the AST. This method is called by the leave() method of the visitor. The method may return this or a new copy of the node which will be installed as a child of the node's parent. The node should not assume that its children have been disambiguated.
